As shown in Fig. 4c, the trap states stemming from deep levels, rather than shallow levels, serve as major recombination centres (ESRH), as the trapped charges there are more likely to be annihilated or recombined with an opposite carrier. In general, the trap-assisted Shockley–Read–Hall (SRH) recombination rate RSRH can be expressed as461RSRH=VthσNtnp−ni2n+p+2nicoshEt−EikBT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
